<i>...that letter brought me
back to earth.</i>

229
00:15:51.285 --> 00:15:53.879
<i>This part of my life is called
''Paying Taxes. ''</i>

230
00:15:55.923 --> 00:15:57.254
<i>If you didn't pay them...</i>

231
00:15:57.458 --> 00:16:00.393
<i>...the government could stick
their hands into your bank account...</i>

232
00:16:01.061 --> 00:16:02.289
<i>...and take your money.</i>

233
00:16:02.496 --> 00:16:03.463
Dad.

234
00:16:03.664 --> 00:16:05.655
<i>No warning. Nothing.</i>

235
00:16:05.866 --> 00:16:08.994
lt can't be too late.
That's my money.

236
00:16:09.203 --> 00:16:12.331
How is somebody just gonna
just take my money?

237
00:16:12.639 --> 00:16:13.936
l was-- l was--

238
00:16:14.141 --> 00:16:17.474
Listen. l--
That's all the money that l have.

239
00:16:17.678 --> 00:16:21.978
You cannot go into my bank acc--
No--

240
00:16:22.182 --> 00:16:24.548
<i>It was the 25th of September.</i>

241
00:16:24.751 --> 00:16:26.446
<i>I remember that day.</i>

242
00:16:26.653 --> 00:16:28.746
<i>Because that's the day
that I found out...</i>

243
00:16:28.956 --> 00:16:34.087
<i>...there was only 2 1 dollars
and 33 cents left in my bank account.</i>

244
00:16:34.294 --> 00:16:35.989
<i>I was broke.</i>

245
00:16:46.340 --> 00:16:48.672
-Dressed yet?
-No.

246
00:16:52.546 --> 00:16:55.879
Chris! Chris!
Don't jerk me around. okay. Chris?

247
00:16:56.083 --> 00:16:58.847
l'm not jerking you around. Ralph.
all right? l'm gonna get it.

248
00:16:59.052 --> 00:17:02.613
-l need that money now. not later.
-When l get it. you get it. Ralph.

249
00:17:02.823 --> 00:17:04.723
Now!

250
00:17:08.362 --> 00:17:10.455
Hey. what's happening. man?

251
00:17:10.697 --> 00:17:13.564
Wayne. l need to get
that $ 1 4 from you.

252
00:17:15.235 --> 00:17:17.100
l thought l didn't owe you that now.

253
00:17:17.304 --> 00:17:20.364
-What? Why?
-Why what?

254
00:17:20.574 --> 00:17:22.940
Why would you think
you don't owe me my money?

255
00:17:23.143 --> 00:17:25.111
l helped you move.

256
00:17:27.347 --> 00:17:30.248
You drove me two blocks. Wayne.

257
00:17:30.450 --> 00:17:32.213
That's 200 yards.

258
00:17:32.419 --> 00:17:34.353
lt's been four months. Wayne.

259
00:17:34.555 --> 00:17:38.150
l need my money. l need my money.
l need my money right now.

260
00:17:38.358 --> 00:17:40.690
-l don't have it. man. l'm sorry.
-Go get my money.

261
00:17:40.894 --> 00:17:43.124
-Wayne. get my mo--
-l really don't. man. lt's $ 1 4.

262
00:17:43.330 --> 00:17:45.025
lt's my $ 1 4!
Go get my money!

263
00:17:45.232 --> 00:17:47.792
-All of this for $ 1 4.
-Get my money. Wayne.

264
00:18:06.153 --> 00:18:08.314
Dad. look at me!

265
00:18:08.755 --> 00:18:10.484
Dad.

266
00:18:11.491 --> 00:18:15.018
-Should l go?
-Sure. man. Why not?

267
00:18:31.078 --> 00:18:32.136
-Stay here.
-Dad. look.

268
00:18:32.346 --> 00:18:33.938
-No. no. Stay right here.
-Dad.

269
00:18:34.147 --> 00:18:36.911
Did you hear what l said?
Did you hear me?

270
00:18:42.022 --> 00:18:45.514
-Dad. where you going?
-Hey. what did l say?

271
00:18:48.562 --> 00:18:50.189
Dad!

272
00:18:50.397 --> 00:18:53.798
Dad. wait! Dad!

273
00:19:01.942 --> 00:19:04.001
-Dad.
-l gotta--

274
00:19:04.211 --> 00:19:07.578
l gotta get back to the '60s. man.
That's what l wanna do.

275
00:19:07.781 --> 00:19:12.081
When l was younger. l wanna see
Jimi Hendrix do that guitar on fire.

276
00:19:15.155 --> 00:19:17.851
Bring back my time machine!

277
00:19:19.192 --> 00:19:20.853
Bring my time machine back!

278
00:19:29.736 --> 00:19:33.331
-Dad. where are we going?
-Just be quiet.

279
00:19:33.940 --> 00:19:36.670
Go get your things. Go.

280
00:19:59.866 --> 00:20:01.561
-Chris?
-Yes.

281
00:20:01.768 --> 00:20:05.670
Dr. Telm can't get back to meet you.
l'm sorry.

282
00:20:16.850 --> 00:20:19.318
Where are we going now?

283
00:20:20.087 --> 00:20:23.352
Gotta-- We gotta
see somebody else.

284
00:20:25.459 --> 00:20:27.586
l'm tired.

285
00:20:29.596 --> 00:20:31.223
l know.

286
00:20:38.605 --> 00:20:42.701
Doesn't seem to be functioning
right now.

287
00:20:43.143 --> 00:20:45.441
-l have to go now. Chris.
-No. no. no.

288
00:20:45.645 --> 00:20:49.513
Just give me a second. l'm sure
l'm gonna be able to figure it out.

289
00:20:51.318 --> 00:20:53.616
Chris. Chris. just come back
when it's working.

290
00:20:53.820 --> 00:20:56.653
-No. no. l have to fix it now.
-No.

291
00:20:56.857 --> 00:21:02.090
Look. l'll still be putting money
in the office. then. all right?

292
00:21:02.295 --> 00:21:04.422
l really have to go. Chris.

293
00:21:05.632 --> 00:21:07.327
Thank you. Thank you.

294
00:21:07.534 --> 00:21:09.399
Thank you for your time.
l appreciate it.

295
00:21:09.603 --> 00:21:11.298
l'll see you soon.

296
00:22:03.290 --> 00:22:05.724
Why are our things here?

297
00:22:06.726 --> 00:22:08.353
Dad.

298
00:22:50.871 --> 00:22:53.601
-Let's go. Come on.
-Where?

299
00:22:55.208 --> 00:22:57.540
-Just out of here.
-Why?

300
00:22:57.744 --> 00:23:00.736
-We can't stay here tonight.
-Yes. we can. Open the door!

301
00:23:00.947 --> 00:23:03.916
-Did you hear what l said? Let's go.
-Open the door!

302
00:23:05.619 --> 00:23:09.487
Hey. did you hear what l said?
Stop it.

303
00:23:09.689 --> 00:23:11.179
Stop it.

304
00:23:15.395 --> 00:23:16.885
Come on.

305
00:23:25.972 --> 00:23:27.462
Come on.

306
00:23:44.457 --> 00:23:46.118
<i>Wayne!</i>

307
00:23:47.193 --> 00:23:49.093
Wayne!

308
00:23:56.269 --> 00:23:58.601
Wayne!

309
00:24:14.120 --> 00:24:17.851
Get up. Stand up. Come on.

310
00:24:33.707 --> 00:24:35.732
Where are we going?

311
00:24:37.911 --> 00:24:41.244
-Dad. where are we going?
-l don't know.

312
00:24:56.730 --> 00:24:59.130
lt's not a time machine.

313
00:24:59.332 --> 00:25:00.765
Dad.

314
00:25:01.134 --> 00:25:02.465
lt's not a time machine.

315
00:25:02.669 --> 00:25:05.934
The guy said it was a time machine.
lt's not a time machine. He was wrong.

316
00:25:06.339 --> 00:25:08.705
-What guy?
-The guy. He was at the park.

317
00:25:08.942 --> 00:25:10.842
He said it was a time machine.

318
00:25:17.150 --> 00:25:18.412
Yes. it is.

319
00:25:19.986 --> 00:25:21.783
No. it's not.

320
00:25:23.790 --> 00:25:25.758
-lt is.
-No. it's not.

321
00:25:31.965 --> 00:25:36.493
All we gotta do is push
this black button right here.

322
00:25:39.672 --> 00:25:40.832
Wanna push it?

323
00:25:45.345 --> 00:25:47.006
Okay.

324
00:25:48.581 --> 00:25:50.139
Come on.

325
00:25:51.651 --> 00:25:53.278
Come on. man.

326
00:25:58.958 --> 00:26:00.016
Right here.

327
00:26:00.427 --> 00:26:02.019
Wait a minute.
Where you wanna go?

328
00:26:02.362 --> 00:26:04.387
l don't know.
Some place from before.

329
00:26:04.931 --> 00:26:06.159
You gotta close your eyes.

330
00:26:06.466 --> 00:26:08.331
You close your eyes. l wanna see.

331
00:26:10.503 --> 00:26:12.937
All right. come on.
We'll push it together.

332
00:26:18.711 --> 00:26:20.542
You gotta close your eyes.
Close your eyes.

333
00:26:21.247 --> 00:26:23.442
lt takes a few seconds.

334
00:26:25.852 --> 00:26:27.752
Oh. my goodness.

335
00:26:27.954 --> 00:26:30.149
Open. open. open!

336
00:26:33.526 --> 00:26:36.188
-What is it?
-Dinosaurs.

337
00:26:36.396 --> 00:26:38.591
-Where?
-You don't see all these dinosaurs?

338
00:26:39.966 --> 00:26:43.629
Look around.
Look at all these dinosaurs.

339
00:26:45.371 --> 00:26:47.771
-Can you see them?
-Yeah.

340
00:26:47.974 --> 00:26:49.373
Wait. Come on. come on.

341
00:26:49.576 --> 00:26:50.907
-Wait. watch out.
-What is it?

342
00:26:51.111 --> 00:26:53.170
Don't step in the fire.
We're cavemen.

343
00:26:53.513 --> 00:26:55.777
We need this fire.
because there's no electricity...

344
00:26:55.982 --> 00:26:57.381
...and it's cold out here. okay?

345
00:26:58.084 --> 00:27:00.450
<i>-Watch out!
-Whoa! Oh. my good-- A T. rex.</i>

346
00:27:00.653 --> 00:27:04.282
Get your stuff.
Get your stuff. Get it.

347
00:27:05.258 --> 00:27:08.352
-We gotta find someplace safe.
-Like what?

348
