-Yeah. l think so.

358
00:28:43.189 --> 00:28:44.816
Hey.

359
00:28:46.392 --> 00:28:48.053
-How you doing. Jay?
-l'm doing good.

360
00:28:48.261 --> 00:28:49.694
How are you getting along?

361
00:28:49.896 --> 00:28:52.091
-Good. l'm good.
-You doing good?

362
00:28:52.298 --> 00:28:54.823
-How you doing?
-l'm doing great.

363
00:28:55.969 --> 00:28:57.596
Where you going?

364
00:29:00.873 --> 00:29:03.899
l-- Sacramento.

365
00:29:04.577 --> 00:29:07.205
Because l'm trying to move
a couple guys from--

366
00:29:07.413 --> 00:29:10.041
They're at PacBell.
and l'm trying to bring them over--

367
00:29:10.250 --> 00:29:11.512
Get them over to us.

368
00:29:11.718 --> 00:29:13.447
So they got me
going out there golfing.

369
00:29:13.653 --> 00:29:15.484
Awesome.

370
00:29:15.688 --> 00:29:17.656
Hey. let them win a round.

371
00:29:22.829 --> 00:29:24.820
Deborah. someone's asking for you.

372
00:29:25.031 --> 00:29:28.125
-Where?
-He's outside. Please come with me.

373
00:29:35.975 --> 00:29:37.533
Hi.

374
00:29:40.880 --> 00:29:43.405
-Can l ask you a question?
-Sure.

375
00:29:45.652 --> 00:29:47.279
We need a room.

376
00:29:47.887 --> 00:29:50.856
Just until l can fix this and sell it.

377
00:29:51.057 --> 00:29:53.685
-There's just some glass work.
-Let me stop you right there.

378
00:29:53.893 --> 00:29:56.361
-l wish l could help you--
-This is my son. Christopher.

379
00:29:56.696 --> 00:29:58.687
-He's 5 years old.
-Hi. baby.

380
00:29:58.898 --> 00:30:01.958
-We need some place to stay.
-Okay. and l would love to help you...

381
00:30:02.168 --> 00:30:05.035
...but we don't take men here.
lt's only women and children.

382
00:30:05.238 --> 00:30:08.298
He can stay here. but you have
to find someplace else to go.

383
00:30:08.508 --> 00:30:09.907
We gotta stay together.

384
00:30:10.109 --> 00:30:11.474
We got-- We're--

385
00:30:11.678 --> 00:30:13.509
-Okay. listen.
-You gotta have some place--

386
00:30:13.713 --> 00:30:16.580
Try Glide Memorial.
The building books up at 5.

387
00:30:16.783 --> 00:30:18.273
So you hurry up. There's a line.

388
00:30:18.484 --> 00:30:21.885
-And where is it? Come on.
-Ellis and Jones.

389
00:30:57.123 --> 00:31:02.755
Hey. everybody. We have
four spots left. and that's all.

390
00:31:03.162 --> 00:31:06.063
-Man.
-Hey. come on. man.

391
00:31:06.265 --> 00:31:07.459
-Come on.
-Come on. what?

392
00:31:07.667 --> 00:31:09.259
-Hey. that's my spot.
-Back off.

393
00:31:09.469 --> 00:31:11.903
Come on. don't do this to me.
Don't--

394
00:31:14.273 --> 00:31:15.831
Dad!

395
00:31:16.275 --> 00:31:18.334
Stop it! Break it up!
Break it up!

396
00:31:18.544 --> 00:31:20.136
Stop! Stop!

397
00:31:20.346 --> 00:31:22.644
Get out of the line. both of you.
Both of you.

398
00:31:22.849 --> 00:31:25.443
l was here first. They told me
that we had to be on time.

399
00:31:25.752 --> 00:31:27.686
l got here on time. l was in line.

400
00:31:27.887 --> 00:31:29.650
l came from work. l got my son.

401
00:31:29.856 --> 00:31:32.381
l was here on time.
We were here on time!

402
00:31:32.592 --> 00:31:34.184
He sliced in front of him in line.

403
00:31:34.394 --> 00:31:36.692
