-He did.

404
00:31:36.963 --> 00:31:41.491
Come on. come on. Rodney.
Come on. Let's go. Get out of line.

405
00:31:50.743 --> 00:31:52.734
That's it. No more.

406
00:31:59.752 --> 00:32:02.721
-What's your favorite color?
-Green.

407
00:32:02.922 --> 00:32:04.184
Green?

408
00:32:04.390 --> 00:32:07.382
-What do you like that's green?
-Trees.

409
00:32:07.593 --> 00:32:10.585
Trees. What else?

410
00:32:10.797 --> 00:32:12.264
Holly.

411
00:32:14.033 --> 00:32:17.992
-Holly. What's holly?
-The Christmas stuff.

412
00:32:18.738 --> 00:32:20.729
Christmas stuff.

413
00:32:21.541 --> 00:32:23.304
What's that?

414
00:32:26.512 --> 00:32:29.413
l guess they want us to go to sleep.

415
00:32:35.988 --> 00:32:40.982
Here you go. We gotta make sure
Captain America's warm in there.

416
00:32:41.427 --> 00:32:43.156
Can you breathe?

417
00:32:43.362 --> 00:32:45.626
-You're good?
-Yeah.

418
00:32:46.065 --> 00:32:48.056
-l gotta go work on the scanner--
-Don't go.

419
00:32:48.267 --> 00:32:51.464
No. no. no. l'm gonna be
right outside the door.

420
00:32:51.671 --> 00:32:55.801
All right? l'm just gonna be right there.
l'll leave the door open a little bit.

421
00:32:56.275 --> 00:32:58.971
And l'll be able to hear you
if you call me.

422
00:32:59.178 --> 00:33:01.669
l wanna go home.

423
00:33:03.749 --> 00:33:07.549
But that's why l gotta
work on the scanner.

424
00:33:08.488 --> 00:33:10.251
All right?

425
00:33:10.456 --> 00:33:12.390
l'm gonna go out there.

426
00:33:12.592 --> 00:33:15.959
l'm gonna leave the door open.
l'll be right up the stairs.

427
00:33:17.063 --> 00:33:18.758
l'll be able to hear you
if you call me.

428
00:33:19.732 --> 00:33:21.859
-All right?
-All right.

429
00:33:22.068 --> 00:33:24.400
You gotta trust me. okay?

430
00:33:24.604 --> 00:33:26.629
You gotta trust me.

431
00:33:27.507 --> 00:33:30.169
l trust you. l trust you.

432
00:33:30.376 --> 00:33:31.809
l trust you.

433
00:33:32.011 --> 00:33:35.003
-l can't hear you.
-l trust you. l trust you.

434
00:33:38.818 --> 00:33:40.547
Give me a kiss.

435
00:33:53.199 --> 00:33:56.168
-l'll just be a little while. okay?
-All right.

436
00:33:56.636 --> 00:33:59.104
-l'll be right here.
-Okay.

437
00:33:59.305 --> 00:34:01.500
-Can you still hear me?
-Yeah.

438
00:34:01.707 --> 00:34:03.197
-Can you hear me?
-Yeah.

439
00:34:03.442 --> 00:34:05.910
-Do you trust me?
-Yeah.

440
00:34:53.125 --> 00:34:54.786
-Yeah.
-Like that?

441
00:34:54.994 --> 00:34:58.657
-Yeah. put that....
-Then you go like that.

442
00:34:58.864 --> 00:35:02.356
-ls that okay?
-l don't know. What do you think?

443
00:35:02.568 --> 00:35:03.626
Good.

444
00:35:04.971 --> 00:35:07.201
Let's go. Get your stuff.

445
00:35:08.441 --> 00:35:11.410
-Hey. why don't you leave it?
-We can't.

446
00:35:11.611 --> 00:35:13.738
We're gonna have
a different room later.

447
00:35:13.946 --> 00:35:15.504
Go.

448
00:35:20.853 --> 00:35:22.218
Hey. Chris.

449
00:35:22.421 --> 00:35:25.754
-Hey. good morning. Mr. Frakesh.
-What's up?

450
00:35:26.792 --> 00:35:27.952
Work trip.

451
00:35:28.160 --> 00:35:30.424
Your wife. Martha. works at
PacBell also. correct?

452
00:35:30.630 --> 00:35:32.393
-Yes. she does.
-And you guys are both...

453
00:35:32.598 --> 00:35:34.259
