Hold that bus! Hold the bus!

464
00:36:08.300 --> 00:36:10.063
My Captain America!

465
00:36:10.302 --> 00:36:12.600
Dad! Dad! Dad!

466
00:36:12.805 --> 00:36:16.070
Stop it! Shut up! Shut up!

467
00:36:18.411 --> 00:36:20.436
-Why don't you let the lady in?
-Hey. back up.

468
00:36:20.646 --> 00:36:23.706
-Hey. man. that's not cool.
-Back up! Back up!

469
00:36:32.024 --> 00:36:33.491
Come on.

470
00:36:36.495 --> 00:36:38.725
Dad. we need to get it!

471
00:36:41.333 --> 00:36:43.961
<i>The important thing about
that freedom train...</i>

472
00:36:44.170 --> 00:36:46.331
<i>...is it's got to climb mountains.</i>

473
00:36:46.539 --> 00:36:49.303
<i>We all have to deal with mountains.</i>

474
00:36:49.508 --> 00:36:52.443
<i>You know. mountains
that go way up high.</i>

475
00:36:52.845 --> 00:36:54.870
And mountains that go
deep and low.

476
00:36:55.081 --> 00:36:56.343
-Amen. preacher!
-Yes.

477
00:36:56.549 --> 00:36:58.847
We know what those mountains are.
here at Glide.

478
00:36:59.151 --> 00:37:01.278
We sing about them.

479
00:37:02.054 --> 00:37:07.583
<i>Lord. don't move that mountain</i>

480
00:37:08.994 --> 00:37:15.422
<i>Give me strength to climb it</i>

481
00:37:15.935 --> 00:37:22.602
<i>Please don't move
That stumbling block</i>

482
00:37:22.808 --> 00:37:29.372
<i>But lead me. Lord. around it</i>

483
00:37:31.016 --> 00:37:36.044
<i>My burdens. they get so heavy</i>

484
00:37:37.890 --> 00:37:43.522
<i>Seems hard to bear</i>

485
00:37:44.463 --> 00:37:48.024
<i>But I won't give up
No. no</i>

486
00:37:48.234 --> 00:37:50.259
<i>Because you promised me</i>

487
00:37:50.469 --> 00:37:57.204
<i>You'd meet me at the altar of prayer</i>

488
00:37:57.409 --> 00:38:04.941
<i>-Lord don't move that mountain
-Please don't move that mountain</i>

489
00:38:05.151 --> 00:38:10.418
<i>But give me strength to climb it</i>

490
00:38:12.658 --> 00:38:14.649
When's your test?

491
00:38:15.861 --> 00:38:17.351
Tomorrow.

492
00:38:21.734 --> 00:38:23.531
Are you ready?

493
00:38:27.439 --> 00:38:28.872
Of course.

494
00:39:07.980 --> 00:39:09.277
Thank you. sir.

495
00:39:18.657 --> 00:39:20.852
-Hey. How you doing?
-Hey.

496
00:39:24.864 --> 00:39:27.856
So did you finish the whole thing.
or you have to go somewhere...?

497
00:39:28.067 --> 00:39:30.535
l have to go somewhere.

498
00:39:31.103 --> 00:39:33.936
-But l finished the whole thing too.
-Oh. good.

499
00:39:34.139 --> 00:39:36.073
-You?
-Yeah.

500
00:39:36.575 --> 00:39:39.544
-How'd you feel about the graphs?
-Easy.

501
00:39:40.546 --> 00:39:44.607
l struggled with the essay question
on the back. What did you write?

502
00:39:44.817 --> 00:39:48.446
-Essay question?
-Yeah. on the back.

503
00:39:58.364 --> 00:39:59.729
Hey. Chris.

504
00:39:59.932 --> 00:40:03.197
-Hey. Jeff. right? 49ers game.
-Yeah.

505
00:40:03.402 --> 00:40:06.894
-Yeah. you were gonna give me a call?
-l never actually got your number.

506
00:40:08.641 --> 00:40:10.609
Here's my number. Call me. okay?

507
00:40:10.809 --> 00:40:13.471
Yes. sir. Absolutely.
Thank you very much.

508
00:40:14.246 --> 00:40:18.012
Chris. you got five bucks?
l left my wallet upstairs.

509
00:40:18.217 --> 00:40:20.481
Let me run up and grab that
for you. Mr. Frohm.

510
00:40:20.686 --> 00:40:23.678
No. l gotta be at CAL Bank at 4.
and l'm late.

511
00:40:29.061 --> 00:40:31.222
-l'll pay you back. honest.
-Five is good?

512
00:40:31.430 --> 00:40:35.059
Five is lovely. Thank you.
Thank you.

513
00:40:48.414 --> 00:40:50.905
That's it. That's the room quota.

514
00:40:51.283 --> 00:40:54.047
There's no more space.
You gotta head out.

515
00:40:54.253 --> 00:40:57.154
That's it for today.
Come back tomorrow.

516
00:40:57.356 --> 00:41:00.348
All the rooms are full.
lt's completely full.

517
00:41:00.559 --> 00:41:04.859
That's it. Just keep heading out.
Come back tomorrow.

518
00:41:39.832 --> 00:41:41.595
You like it?

519
00:42:32.651 --> 00:42:36.314
Twenty. One. two. three. four.

520
00:42:39.425 --> 00:42:43.020
Now. here's your bulb.
and there's your ferrite core inductor.

521
00:42:43.228 --> 00:42:46.026
-How much?
-Eight dollars.

522
00:42:47.132 --> 00:42:50.465
-What's that?
-lt's to repair the light.

523
00:42:50.669 --> 00:42:52.694
Can l see it?

524
00:42:54.606 --> 00:42:57.666
Yeah. sure. Just don't break it.

525
00:42:57.876 --> 00:43:02.370
Unless you wanna sleep in a room
with me for the rest of your life.

526
00:43:03.582 --> 00:43:05.447
l don't mind.

527
00:43:05.918 --> 00:43:07.749
Yeah. you will.

528
00:43:24.036 --> 00:43:26.402
Why don't you
get some sleep. okay?

529
00:43:26.605 --> 00:43:27.765
Okay.

530
00:43:27.973 --> 00:43:31.067
-Warm enough?
-Yeah.

531
00:43:31.343 --> 00:43:33.004
All right.

532
00:43:35.114 --> 00:43:38.015
Did Mom leave because of me?

533
00:43:41.353 --> 00:43:45.551
-What?
-Did Mom leave because of me?

534
00:43:50.129 --> 00:43:54.657
Don't-- Don't even think
something like that.

535
00:43:55.734 --> 00:43:57.861
Mom left because of Mom.

536
00:43:58.070 --> 00:44:00.334
And you didn't have anything
to do with that. okay?

537
00:44:01.039 --> 00:44:02.939
Okay.

538
00:44:12.784 --> 00:44:14.843
You're a good papa.

539
00:44:22.694 --> 00:44:24.685
All right. go to sleep.

540
00:44:25.497 --> 00:44:28.432
-l love you.
-l love you too.

541
00:45:24.890 --> 00:45:26.881
So far. so good. Chris.

542
00:45:32.965 --> 00:45:35.525
-lt works.
-Thank you very much.

543
00:45:35.734 --> 00:45:39.568
<i>Two hundred and fifty dollars.
Four more weeks of oxygen.</i>

544
00:45:39.905 --> 00:45:44.137
One hundred. 20. 40. 60. 80. 200.

545
00:45:44.343 --> 00:45:47.107
Twenty. 30. 40. 50.

546
00:45:48.247 --> 00:45:49.874
-Anything else?
-No. sir.

547
00:45:50.082 --> 00:45:51.413
Thank you. Thank you.

548
00:45:51.617 --> 00:45:53.551
-You ready?
-Yep.

549
00:45:55.487 --> 00:45:58.388
-Are we going to the church place?
-No.

550
00:45:58.590 --> 00:46:00.558
Where are we going. then?

551
00:46:01.360 --> 00:46:03.920
-Probably stay at a hotel.
-A hotel?

552
00:46:04.129 --> 00:46:05.187
Just for the night.

553
00:46:05.397 --> 00:46:08.161
We can go back to the cave
if you like.

554
00:46:08.367 --> 00:46:10.096
No. thank you.

555
00:46:10.302 --> 00:46:12.827
-Ever?
-l hope not.

556
00:46:13.038 --> 00:46:14.505
Why not?

557
00:46:14.706 --> 00:46:17.504
Well. because some things are fun
the first time you do them...

558
00:46:17.709 --> 00:46:20.041
...and then not so much the next.

559
00:46:20.245 --> 00:46:23.146
-Like the bus?
-Yeah. like the bus.

560
00:46:23.348 --> 00:46:26.545
<i>I'm sorry. I shouldn't laugh.
should I?</i>

561
00:46:39.564 --> 00:46:41.259
<i>Sometimes when we're moving
at night...</i>

562
00:46:41.466 --> 00:46:44.196
<i>...we pass houses with lights
and people.</i>

563
00:46:44.970 --> 00:46:46.835
<i>Sometimes you can
hear them laugh.</i>

564
00:46:52.244 --> 00:46:55.611
<i>The next day. after work...</i>

565
00:46:55.814 --> 00:46:58.044
<i>...we just went to the beach.</i>

566
00:46:58.250 --> 00:47:00.150
<i>Far away from anything.</i>

567
00:47:00.352 --> 00:47:01.717
<i>Everything.</i>

568
00:47:01.920 --> 00:47:03.581
<i>Just Christopher and me.</i>

569
00:47:05.223 --> 00:47:07.589
-Did you see me?
-Yeah.

570
00:47:07.793 --> 00:47:10.887
<i>Far away from buses and noise...</i>

571
00:47:11.096 --> 00:47:16.728
<i>...and a constant disappointment
in my ten-gallon head...</i>

572
00:47:17.903 --> 00:47:19.768
<i>...and myself.</i>

573
00:47:20.372 --> 00:47:22.738
-Chris. thank you very much.
-Well. thank you. Dean.

574
00:47:22.941 --> 00:47:24.772
-Take care.
-You made all the right moves.

575
00:47:24.976 --> 00:47:26.500
Thanks. Chris.

576
00:47:28.580 --> 00:47:29.911
<i>Because when I was young...</i>

577
00:47:30.115 --> 00:47:33.881
<i>...and I'd get an A on a history test
or whatever...</i>

578
00:47:34.086 --> 00:47:38.682
<i>...I'd get this good feeling about
all the things that I could be.</i>

579
00:47:40.592 --> 00:47:44.221
<i>And then I never became
any of them.</i>

580
00:47:51.737 --> 00:47:54.262
-Hey. Chris.
-Hey.

581
00:47:54.473 --> 00:47:57.101
-How you doing. Jay?
-l'm doing fine.

582
00:47:57.309 --> 00:48:01.439
Rumor has it you signed 31 accounts
for us from Pacific Bell.

583
00:48:01.646 --> 00:48:03.079
Yeah. yeah.

584
00:48:03.281 --> 00:48:07.081
Met some guys at a ball game.
got some cards. l've been working.

585
00:48:07.285 --> 00:48:08.912
l guess.

586
00:48:11.890 --> 00:48:14.120
So one more day.

587
00:48:14.326 --> 00:48:15.918
Getting nervous?

588
00:48:16.495 --> 00:48:18.861
-No. l'm okay.
-Yeah?

589
00:48:19.064 --> 00:48:20.998
Listen. whatever happens...

590
00:48:21.199 --> 00:48:23.633
...you've done a fantastic job. Chris.

591
00:48:23.835 --> 00:48:25.393
l mean that.

592
00:48:26.238 --> 00:48:28.069
Take care of yourself.

593
00:48:43.054 --> 00:48:46.251
Yes. Mr. Johnson.
Chris Gardner. Dean Witter.

594
00:48:46.558 --> 00:48:48.651
Yes. sir. Just calling
to thank you very much...

595
00:48:48.860 --> 00:48:51.351
...for your support
at last month's seminar.

596
00:48:51.897 --> 00:48:53.558
Yes. sir. Absolutely.

597
00:48:54.199 --> 00:48:55.826
Yes. sir.

598
00:48:56.034 --> 00:48:57.399
No. sir. that's it.

599
00:48:57.602 --> 00:49:00.093
Thank you very much. Bye-bye.

600
00:49:01.706 --> 00:49:04.573
Chris. Come.

601
00:49:31.970 --> 00:49:35.064
-Hi. Chris.
-Mr. Frohm. good to see you.

602
00:49:36.208 --> 00:49:38.142
-Nice shirt.
-Thank you. sir.

603
00:49:38.343 --> 00:49:39.537
-Chris.
-Hey. Jay.

604
00:49:39.978 --> 00:49:44.244
-Chris.
-Chris. sit down. please.

605
00:49:47.185 --> 00:49:51.246
l thought l'd wear a shirt today.

606
00:49:51.456 --> 00:49:53.424
You know.
being the last day and all.

607
00:49:53.625 --> 00:49:56.958
Well. thank you. Thank you.
We appreciate that.

608
00:49:57.863 --> 00:49:59.626
But...

609
00:49:59.831 --> 00:50:02.629
...wear one tomorrow though. okay?

610
00:50:02.834 --> 00:50:05.769
Because tomorrow's
going to be your first day...

611
00:50:06.505 --> 00:50:09.736
...if you'd like to work here
as a broker.

612
00:50:11.076 --> 00:50:12.907
Would you like that. Chris?

613
00:50:13.812 --> 00:50:15.404
Yes. sir.

614
00:50:15.614 --> 00:50:18.981
Good. We couldn't be happier.

615
00:50:19.951 --> 00:50:23.114
So welcome.

616
00:50:24.990 --> 00:50:29.984
-Was it as easy as it looked?
-No. sir. No. sir. it wasn't.

617
00:50:32.330 --> 00:50:34.730
-Good luck. Chris.
-Thank you. Thank you.

618
00:50:41.139 --> 00:50:43.004
Oh. Chris.

619
00:50:45.510 --> 00:50:47.603
l almost forgot.

620
00:50:49.648 --> 00:50:51.206
Thank you.

621
00:51:11.603 --> 00:51:13.798
<i>This part of my life...</i>

622
00:51:14.706 --> 00:51:16.901
<i>...this little part...</i>

623
00:51:20.245 --> 00:51:22.873
<i>...is called ''Happiness. ''</i>

624
00:52:09.594 --> 00:52:13.223
Christopher. Christopher.
Come here.

625
00:52:42.894 --> 00:52:45.294
So how many...

626
00:52:45.497 --> 00:52:47.431
...planets are there?

627
00:52:48.733 --> 00:52:50.530
-Seven.
-Seven?

628
00:52:51.036 --> 00:52:52.867
Nine.

629
00:52:55.240 --> 00:52:57.299
Who's the king of the jungle?

630
00:52:57.709 --> 00:53:00.439
-Gorilla.
-The gorilla?

631
00:53:00.745 --> 00:53:02.144
The gorilla?

632
00:53:02.347 --> 00:53:04.008
No. Lion.

633
00:53:04.215 --> 00:53:06.809
Oh. yeah. Lion. lion. lion.

634
00:53:08.887 --> 00:53:11.879
Hey. Dad. listen to this.
Knock. knock.

635
00:53:12.090 --> 00:53:14.024
-Who's there?
-Shelby.

636
00:53:14.225 --> 00:53:15.317
Shelby who?

637
00:53:15.527 --> 00:53:19.327
<i>Shelby coming around the mountain
When she comes</i>

638
00:53:20.165 --> 00:53:21.530
-Knock knock.
-Who's there?

639
00:53:21.733 --> 00:53:24.201
-Nobody.
-Nobody who?

640
00:53:25.103 --> 00:53:26.866
Nobody who?

641
00:53:30.175 --> 00:53:33.144
Now. that's funny. l like that one.
